<DOC><DOCNO> AP880505-0332 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-05-88 1438EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u f BC-Britain-Stocks 1stLd-Writethru   05-05 0178</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru,0184</SECOND><HEAD>London Shares Close Lower</HEAD><NOTE>Eds: Rewrites thruout to UPDATE with closing stock prices</NOTE><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Share prices on the London Stock Exchange droppedThursday as the market fell victim to declining prices on WallStreet.   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed down5.2 points, or 0.28 percent, to 1,789.5.   Share prices had opened slightly lower but picked up some steamat midmorning following reports of favorable company earnings.   But by midafternoon, London stocks began to feel some of thepressure from Wall Street's soggy opening and drifted lower.   Some London dealers said computer-generated program-selling onWall Street, which accounted for a sharp loss Wednesday, lingeredin the market Thursday. By the close of London trading, WallStreet's most widely watched index, the Dow Jones industrialaverage, was down 17.91 points at 2,018.40.   Pervasive nervousness also contributed to the London selloff,dealers said, after Wednesday's news that the British Department ofTrade and Industry would refer the Kuwait Investment Officepurchase of British Petroleum Co. shares to the Mergers andMonopolies Commission.</TEXT></DOC>